</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,674,1168,1195]" box="[189,674,1168,1195]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
LENGTH. Body 
<quantity box="[362,448,1168,1194]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
, wing 6.5–7.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,1399,1233,1471]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
HEAD (
<figureCitation box="[274,372,1233,1260]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatrigon spp., head, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E–F. M.natalensissp. nov.(arrow =postocellarspot)(♁).G.M.sexmaculatus sp. nov.(♁).H. M.apiformis sp. nov. (♁). I. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). J. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). K. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). L. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). M. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀). Symbol: x = postocellar spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849882/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs 2D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[392,427,1233,1260]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">3D</figureCitation>
). Upper part of face across the whole width, at the level and below antennae, completely covered with microtrichia, thereby microtrichiose stripes along eye margin and median facial stripe connected at that level; frons and vertex shiny (only few microtrichia in the middle of frons, anterior and lateral to anterior ocella), without postocellar spots or with very few microtrichia; microtrichia on post-ocular orbit do not exceed post-ocular ridge; length of post-ocular orbit large, 0.11– 0.13 × width of head; distance between eyes large, 0.21–0.23 width of head; ocellar triangle equilateral and without median groove.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,1399,1510,1607]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
THORAX (
<figureCitation box="[299,391,1510,1536]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[291,1281,1100,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[291,1281,1100,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Megatrigon spp., mesoscutum, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). B. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). C. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). D. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849890/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum with two wide, distinct, long, lateral microtrichiose stripes, two long submedian microtrichiose stripes ending far beyond level of transverse suture, and weak prescutellar microtrichia; supra-alar setae yellow; median about 0.5 of width of mediotergite covered by microtrichia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,1398,1646,1707]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">WING. Membrane not infuscated, veins and microtrichia light brown, cell br above vena spuria almost all covered with microtrichia; costagium with yellow setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,1399,1746,1808]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
LEGS (
<figureCitation box="[260,352,1746,1773]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,1586,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,1586,1898]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 6. Megatrigon spp., metafemur, ♁ (SEM). A. Megatrigon argentifrons sp. nov., proximal half posterodorsally with striae (arrow). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov., enlarged striae. C. M. magnicornis sp. nov., anteroventral preapical flange." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849898/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Setae on legs all yellow; pro- and mesotibia with indistinct dark submedian ring; all tarsi yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,1398,1847,2014]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation box="[315,408,1847,1874]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Megatrigon spp., habitus, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849878/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs 1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[421,457,1848,1874]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1862,1888]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Megatrigon spp., abdomen, dorsal view, ♁. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849902/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">7D</figureCitation>
). Tergites 2+3 and posterior margin of tergite 4 brown-yellow with black alveoli, setae on tergites short, yellow and in some parts black: posterior 0.25 of tergite 2, submedian and posterior part of tergite 3; tergite 2 medially covered with white microtrichia, tergite 3 with tiny microtrichiose line extended from anterior margin to the centre of tergite, tergite 4 without microtrichiose spots. Male genitalia in 
<figureCitation box="[327,436,1988,2014]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1825,1851]" captionTargetBox="[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 10. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, epandrium, left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. Megatrigon sp. from sexfasciatus group. M. M. nivalis. Symbols: x = ventral margin of median surstyle; y = posterior surstyle; z = cercus; w = subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849914/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs 10D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[451,500,1988,2014]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium (A–M) and phallus (N), left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. sp. from sexfasciatus group. M–N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = hamus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849918/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">11D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[515,565,1988,2014]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1794,1820]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 12. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium, ventral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. apiformis sp. nov. G. M. cooksoni sp. nov. H. M. immaculatus sp. nov. I. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. J. M. tabanoides sp. nov. K. Megatrigon sp. from the sexfasciatus group. L. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = lateral ‘shoulders’." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849922/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">12D</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
